description: We hope you're ready for some belly laughs, because the newest issue of MAD features our full-length spoof of Mike & Molly! We also sink our teeth into smartphone etiquette, The Hunger Games and More Movie Mash-ups! And here's some MORE food for thought – there's also "MAD's Make Your Own Twilight Movie," the Fundalini Pages, Spy vs. Spy, The MAD Strip Club, Planet Tad!!!!!, The MAD Fold-In, Sergio Aragonés' MAD Look at the Filthy Rich and so much more! It's completely stuffed! We've got a gut feeling you're going to love it!
name: Mike & Molly

description:
What is lost in life is found in...death!

In a not too distant future torn apart by a deadly biological catastrophe, doctors Richard and Gabriella Adams stood on the verge of a scientific breakthrough—a cure to the epidemic spreading across North America, splitting the population between those that are plagued—and those in power that are not. However, their union of research and marriage is tragically ripped in two, and Richard soon discovers that he has to sacrifice everything in order to piece together a hope for humanity and put the shattered remains of his life back together again.

In a United States reeling from the aftereffects of a biological weapon detonated over the Gulf of Mexico, Doctors Gabriella and Richard Adams are hired to develop a cure for the effects of the bomb. Unfortunately, as they seek to invent a cure, they create a horrible monster. Through a dual narrative — one following the pasts of Gabriella and Richard and one following the monster — "Broken Pieces" will slowly reveal the full story of what happened and why
Can Deadzone take down a corrupt pharmaceutical businessman with the aid of a sultry, new partner? Or, will the partner double cross Deadzone in order to cash in with the highest bidder?
name: Not So Special

description: ALTER EGO #89 presents a special issue on Harvey Comics’ pre-Code horror mags of the 1950s! Behind a dynamic cover featuring JOE SIMON & JACK KIRBY’s Stuntman—and HOWARD NOSTRAND horror—you’ll find: interviews with SID JACOBSON, WARREN KREMER, and HOWARD NOSTRAND (on his work with BOB POWELL)—plus Harvey artist KEN SELIG talks to JIM AMASH! Mr. Monster presents the wit and wisdom (and worse) of DR. FREDRIC WERTHAM—plus FCA (Fawcett Collectors of America) with C.C. Beck and Marc Swayze, BILL SCHELLY & MARVIN GILES on Detroit’s Triple Fan Fairs, and more! Edited by Roy Thomas.
